# Manual example 2 (switch.md:52): one input to four outputs. A forward trigger
# moves the ACTIVE output BACKWARD (O1->O4->O3...). With only input1 patched
# (inputs 2..4 read 0 V), only the output currently pointing at input1 carries
# the signal; all others emit 0 V. `input` is the synonym for `input1`.
patch <<<
[switch]
    input = I1
    output1 = O1
    output2 = O2
    output3 = O3
    output4 = O4
    forward = I8
>>>
@0 set I1 0.5
@0 expect O1 0.5
@0 expect O2 0
@0 expect O3 0
@0 expect O4 0
@1 set I8 1
@1 expect O1 0
@1 expect O2 0
@1 expect O3 0
@1 expect O4 0.5
@2 set I8 0
@3 set I8 1
@3 expect O1 0
@3 expect O2 0
@3 expect O3 0.5
@3 expect O4 0
